Job Descriptions:


Manage cycle counts process on a regular basis;
Investigate discrepancies in reported quantities and locations of all inventory;
Prepare weekly inventory report;
Perform stock reconciliation to minimize variance  & loss;
Assist in company stock take preparation, arrangement and follow-up actions;
Support to system development; and
Perform other duties and responsibilities as assigned.

 Job Requirements:

Degree holder with a major in Supply Chain Management or Logistics Management;
At least 5 years of relevant experience in supply chain management and in retail industry is preferred;
Independent, analytical, self-motivated with strong numerical sense and logical thinking;
Hardworking, organized and with a strong sense of responsibility, able to work independently under pressure and meet deadline with high accuracy;
Excellent command of both written and spoken English and Chinese (Cantonese and Mandarin); and
Familiar with Microsoft Excel, Word, power point and Chinese Word Processing.
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Senior Officer


